article.headline: Stony Brook 86, UMBC 72
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Muhammad El-Amin scored 26 points to lead Stony Brook to an 86-72 victory over Maryland-Baltimore County on Tuesday night, extending the Seawolves' winning streak to eight games. El-Amin was 10-for-17 from the field and Chris Martin added 17 points as Stony Brook (19-7, 11-2 America East Conference) moved to one game ahead of Vermont in the conference standings. El-Amin scored seven points to key a 19-5 run as Stony Brook turned a 38-34 halftime lead into a 57-39 advantage with 12:28 remaining. After UMBC's Chris De La Rosa hit two free throws, Stony Brook's Bryan Dougher hit a 3-pointer for a 60-41 with 11:57 to play. The Seawolves shot 51.8 percent from the floor (29-for-56). Dougher finished with 14 points and Tommy Brenton had 10 points and 11 rebounds. De La Rosa scored 20, Shawn Grant 17, Robbie Jackson 12 and Matt Spadafora 10 points for UMBC (3-24, 2-12).
